pdf generates a probability density plot of a variable 
from an ensemble of datasets



usage: pdf -v <variable> [-l <level>] [-h] [-t <timeslice>] [-b <bin-size>] [-s <stencil diameter>] [-o <outputfile>] <input sccm history files>
   -v : name of variable to extract from the input files
   -l : index of level to process (if not specified, all levels will be processed)
   -h : show histogram on stdout
   -t : index of timeslice to process (if not specified, all timeslices will be processed)
   -b : bin size (default divides range into10 equal bins)
   -s : stencil size in level and time dimension (default is 1)
   -o : name of output file (if not specified, output will be in pdf.<pid>.nc)

